        </h1>
        <p class="font-serif text-lg text-[#676767] dark:text-white">
            I am a software developer, writer, and an undergraduate student at the Java Institute For Advanced Technology. I spend most of my time reading books and articles.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-serif text-lg text-[#676767] dark:text-white">
            I am a co-founder of Ruzzz, a software development company that builds e-commerce solutions for small and medium-sized businesses. And unfortunately, I cannot share much about it at the moment. more to come soon.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-serif text-lg text-[#676767] dark:text-white">
            Specifically, I am a passionate Backend Developer who loves solving complex problems. With a knack for building efficient and scalable systems. I do frontend too, but I prefer to work on the backend.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mt-8">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
            <h1
                class="font-sans text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#2e3440] dark:text-white"
            >
                I write ‚å®Ô∏è
            </h1>
            <a
                href="/blog"
                class="text-[#2e3440] font-semibold underline dark:text-white"
            >
                All posts
            </a>
        </div>
        <p class="py-4 font-serif text-lg text-[#676767] dark:text-white">
            Here are some of my recent posts. And If you are wondering what I write
            about, I write about software development, productivity, and
            personal growth.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc">
            {
                posts.map((post) => {
                    return (
                        <li class="pt-3">
                            <a
                                href={`/blog/${post.slug}`}
                                class="font-serif text-lg text-[#2e3440] hover:underline dark:text-white"
                            >
                                {post.data.title}
